	   <tr><td colspan=2>Simply because I don't like having to crunch obscene amounts of numbers to see how new gear will affect me, I have a simple philosophy:<br><br>If it keeps me from getting beat on, me like.<br><br>If it hits really hard, me like.<br><br>If it makes me swing more, me like.<br><br>*shrug*<br><br>And as for affecting double attack, one would think the roll for the skill working would be the same on every single swing.&nbsp;&nbsp;So you're swinging a 20/30 weapon MAYBE twice a round, and when you hit for max damage on both hits, then it can be a really big hit, but if you miss twice, then.  *shrug*<br><br>I realize I'm stating the obvious, but I don't think double attack should be worried about when you're dealing with haste.  Just treat your weapon as if it would only swing once (Because you may have a string of bad luck and see your Double Attack work maybe once in a fight) and I think you'd do fine.  *shrug*<br><br>As for equations, I may be good at math, but all these give me a headache, and I'm not afraid to admit it.<br><br>For the record, I'm working on gaining a haste item, but my Mith and my Centi Warspear are fast enough for now, and I'm a cheap pally; right now, I'm saving up for better armor.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Feb  6 21:25:49 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonfury<br>Crusader of the Burning Heart, 60th Protection, Third Blessing<br>Fennin Ro<br>New Dawnings<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479</a></td></tr>
