	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your point is taken but what I think you missed from my post is that I'm trying to determine a *ratio*.&nbsp;&nbsp;Like you said, you can have a string of misses with double attack, but for that matter you can have a string of misses on regular attack.  Then what does it matter whether you're using a Mith 2hs or Centi WS or a Rusty Short sword?  The ratio is just an indicator of what you can expect to do on average.  <br><br>I know it seems trivial but here's a nice example of how it comes into play:  <br><br>Take the Mith 2hs (21/40) and the BABS (24/39).  AFTER the haste effect, here are the two ratios of these two swords:<br><br>Mith 2hs - 1.619<br>BABS - 1.625<br><br>In a nutshell, over time these swords are practically identical in terms of the damage they will do.  But on my server, a Mith 2hs goes for about 800p and a BABS can be had for about 100p.  And don't forget that Centi Warspear which has them both beat with a ratio of 1.5 and can be had for about 200p.  <br><br>So for me, before I spend a few days worth of plat on a sword, I think it's worth it to take five minutes and do the math first.  :-)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
