	   <a name=101249741138126></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101249741138126><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101249741138126>Paladin Disciplines 51+</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=101249741138126#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 31st 1:18 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Paladins,<br><br>I thought I'd post the &quot;Paladin Disciplines&quot; that you begin to receive at level 51.&nbsp;&nbsp;No one ever explained disciplines to me and I didn't know if you had to buy them or train for them or do something special to get them.  Well, come to find out you don't have to do anything to get them.  Once you reach the level, you have them. It's that easy!  At level 54, I finally learned how to use a discipline, even though I had had one for 3+ levels!  Don't let this happen to you!<br><br>Now granted, I didn't miss a whole lot as the level 51 Discipline: Resistant, isn't all that great, but I certainly would have used it once or twice had I known I actually had it and didn't have to do anything to use it but type: /disc Resistant!<br><br>Disciplines:<br><br>Name: Resistant<br>Level: 51<br>Activate: /disc resistant<br>Duration: 1 Minute<br>Reuse Time: 1 Hour<br><br>This discipline adds +10 to all resistances for 1 minute.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as you level. <br><br>*This is nice if you are just about to engage a Dragon or fighting in ToV and need a boost for some special mob, etc. +10 to all saves never hurts.<br><br>**************************************************<br><br>Name: Fearless<br>Level: 54<br>Activate: /disc Fearless<br>Duration: 11 Seconds<br>Reuse Time: 1 Hour<br><br>Immunity to &amp;#8220;Fear&amp;#8221; and all spells that cause &amp;#8220;Fear&amp;#8221;. This discipline lasts for 11 seconds, and has a base reuse time of 1 hour. The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as you level. <br><br>* This spell is handy when getting ready to engage a Dragon that fears or to take down Miragul the Lich Necro in the Everfrost Caves for the Avenger Sword quest drops.  First thing Miragul did to me was hit me with a Life Tap for 1500 pts, then...he Feared me.<br><br>**************************************************<br><br>Name: Holyforge<br>Level: 55<br>Activate: /disc Holyforge<br>Duration: 2 Minutes<br>Reuse Time: 72 Minutes<br><br>Critical Hits and Crippling Blows versus Undead with an increased probability of going off. This discipline lasts for 2 minutes and has a base reuse time of 72 minutes.<br><br>* A nice boost when facing that tough Undead mob.  I used it when facing the 4th Boss Mob in the Ring of Fire in Acryllia.  I also use it occasionally when soloing Undead in places like Karnor's Castle, etc.<br><br>**************************************************<br><br>Name: Sanctification<br>Level: 60<br>Activate: /disc Sanctification (That's a guess)<br>Duration: 10 Seconds<br>Reuse Time: 72 Minutes<br><br>This discipline gives immunity to most types of harmful spells. This discipline will last for 10 seconds, and has a base reuse time of 72 minutes. <br><br>* Obviously I haven't got to try this one yet! I assume you will activate it the same way you did all the others. Maybe Praetor can chime in and confirm. I can see a use for this. Most often, mobs use their most powerful spells when first attacked. If you could avoid that big Nuke, that could be handy.<br><br>And there you have it! The Paladin Disciplines. Compared to some, like Warriors, our Disciplines are not the best, but they do have their uses.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
