	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 31st 10:56 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Raynes,<br><br>You should definitely pick-up a 1-hs weapon to train that skill. While you may not use it very much, you should still keep it trained up. It is much harder to try and build a skill that you have neglected for 10+ levels than it is to keep it current as you go along. Since you have a mithril 2-hand sword already, that weapon is going to serve you better than most 1-hs weapons...at least for now. Pick up a FAST 1-hs weapon so you can build the skill quickly and get back to your mithril 2-hander as soon as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't forget about 1-hb and piercing either. Work on them a little here and there so they don't get too far behind.<br><br>At level 23, most folks go to Lake of Ill Omen for experience.  From what I understand, LOIO is a great place to XP. I never went there, however.  I spent my 20's mostly in the Estate of Unrest fighting undead. At level 23, you have all the skills you need to be a force against undead. You have Ward Undead and Invisibility to Undead.  Unrest takes some getting used to but it's a great zone for Paladins. You now have Ward Undead and Invisibility to Undead. You can solo mobs on the first floor with some practice, but groups should be easy to find too.  The run through Dagnor's Cauldron can be hazardous if you meet up with a Tidal Lord, but otherwise, it's a great zone, lots of fun, good XP, and good drops for cash.<br><br>You can also try the lake/ramp/entrance area of Mistmoore, but you will need a group for this. The dark elves there are tough!<br><br>Good Luck!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
