	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay so let this be a lesson to all you newbies Paldins. <br>1. Keep a decent set of wis gear built up for situations when you need to heal.<br>2. Dont let your spell skills slip for healing.<br><br>Also on a side note healing an incoming puller is super for gaining aggro and keeping aggro off the cleric. I always tell clerics let me get first heal in on incoming puller. <br><br>If there are adds this usually brings adds to me which gives a little seperation and makes it easier on the enchanter. Easier to pick out individual mobs and less broken mezzes.<br>Also heal puller then hit assist button followed up by a stun you almost never have a mob go after the cleric .<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
