	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All,<br><br>I have a current running debate with a guy in my immediate group concerning 2 handed weapons and bash.&nbsp;&nbsp;I haven't spent much time on 2-handed weapon skills, because I feel I need the extra hits and periodic stunning that bash gives.  Not to mention the extra AC the shield gives me.<br><br>I'm a lowbie (level 15), and don't have access to a lot of cash to get uber 2-handed weapons, although I was given a Messenger of the Queen or something like that, (2HP, 20dam, 40delay).<br><br>Here are my arguments:<br><br>2-handed weapons: Yick.  High damage, but slow recycle times and if you miss you have to wait forever to try again.<br><br>Shield/bash: Quicker strikes and more chances at damage, even if it is slightly lower.  Extra attack/damage in form of bash (however little, it still counts), extra AC from the shield, more items = more item buffs (eventually).<br><br>So... what's the consensus and reasons... 2-handed weapons, or shield/bash?<br><br>Thanks!<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Jan 28 15:19:49 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Z.<br>- Zegophon - 16th Ranger<br>- Zegaria - 15th Paladin<br>- Zegog - 14th Warrior</td></tr>
